  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for an initial 15 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/378.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/378.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/378.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/378.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/378.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and finely chop</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the<strong> chopped leek </strong>and 30ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[60ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong>, then cook for 3 min or until the water has evaporated</p><p>Once evaporated, transfer the <strong>cooked leek </strong>onto a plate and leave to cool completely (reserve the pan for later!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663253204994-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663253204994-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663253204994-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663253204994-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663253204994-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, separate the <strong>egg</strong> <strong>yolk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>from the <strong>white<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> by cracking the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>over a shallow bowl and catching the <strong>yolk</strong> in the shell</p><p>Transfer the <strong>yolk</strong> from one shell half to the other several times, until all the <strong>whites</strong> are in the bowl and you are left with the yolk in the shell, then transfer the <strong>yolk</strong> to a separate shallow bowl</p><p>Grate the<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1663253212357-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1663253212357-x400.jpg",
